      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get the \"universal\" angle, but as a strategist, i need more concrete direction for the casting directors. \"polished\" and \"gravitas\" can be interpreted a hundred different ways. \n\nif we're talking about that \"inherited legacy\" look you mentioned, aren't there certain demographics that historically carry that weight more naturally in the luxury market? like, if we're casting for a campaign that feels established and generational, wouldn't it be more authentic to focus on European or Western-coded archetypes rather than, say, emerging markets? i just want to make sure we aren't diluting the brand's perceived prestige by being too broad.",
